  <preparation>Put apples into a deep casserole.  Combine 1/4 cup sugar and the water in a saucepan; bring to boil.  

Pour syrup over apples.  Cover casserole and bake at 350F 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender, basting occasionally.  

Pour ale into a saucepan and heat on low heat until it foams.  

Add spices, sherry and 1 1/2 cups sugar, lemon peel and lemon juice.  Heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.  

Remove from heat and allow to cool for 20 minutes. 

Reheat mixture and pour through a double thickness of cheesecloth into a heat resistant punch bowl.  Float apples and serve, garnished with lemon peel.</preparation>
